    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-12-13T04:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-12-13T04:00:00-05:00" n="528"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d528">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/12–1348: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Peiping</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Clubb</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-12-13T17:00:00+08:00"
                            >December 13, 1948—5 p. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received December 14—2:27 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>533. Remytel 531, December 13. Military situation west Hopeh deteriorating
                    rapidly with Nankow reported lost, CAF departed west field with rifle and
                    machine gun fire audible west Peiping suburbs. Tungchow American school
                    evacuated great part Peiping today.</p>
                <p>Chin Feng-chuan (director education and cultural committee Fu’s headquarters) is
                    quoted as saying Peiping will be defended.</p>
                <p>Nationalist troops which had been stationed Nankow arriving west suburbs
                    today.</p>
                <p>Sent Dept, repeated Nanking 787, Tientsin.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Clubb</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
